The paper deals with cardinality estimation in relational databases, which is a core problem in database systems and falls under the scope of cs.DB. The proposed solution involves the use of deep autoregressive models, which are a type of machine learning model and thus relate to cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also discusses Monte Carlo integration, which is a statistical technique and falls under the scope of cs.IT. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on real-world datasets, which involves data analysis and falls under the scope of cs.DS.
